  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>red potato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped potato</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, 3/4 of your<strong> dried oregano </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>on a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) then put in the oven for an initial 20 min or until tender – <strong>these are your smoky potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
